Draghi: Benefits of single currency can only be reaped with national and European policies/institutions that ensure it works for everyone
Draghi: Real estate price growth remains moderate in euro area. Asset price developments are not accompanied by increasing leverage.
Draghi: Measures might lower interest margins but improve credit quality of firms & households and increase value of financial assets held
Draghi: Effects of our measures on bank profitability tend to largely offset each other
Draghi: Benefits of our policy clearly outweigh potential side effects. Our measures have played a key role in preserving stability
Draghi: Support from our monetary policy measures is still needed if inflation rates are to converge towards objective in sustained manner
Draghi: We need to continue on this path so that unemployment decreases further and more Europeans can benefit from recovery
Draghi: Over last two years GDP per capita increased by 3%, unemployment has fallen to lowest level since May 2009, debt to GDP declining
Draghi: To achieve objective of EMU (the “economic and social progress” of the Maastricht Treaty) we need sustained growth and job creation
Draghi: Raison d’être of European project was to keep us united when it is tempting to turn against neighbours or seek national solutions
Draghi: With the single currency, we have forged bonds that survived the worst economic crisis since the Second World War
